  "body": "PR https://github.com/ChainSafe/lodestar/pull/2112 adds a C++ script to collect GC metrics. This script breaks when run in a worker apparently, which happens on the multi-thread test.\r\n\r\nHowever, metrics SHOULD be disabled by default and should no be loaded on the multi-thread test.\r\n\r\n```\r\n2021-02-28 18:15:31 [NODE 2]           warn: Low peer count peers=0\r\nFATAL ERROR: HandleScope::HandleScope Entering the V8 API without proper locking in place\r\n 1: 0x9dab70 node::Abort() [/opt/hostedtoolcache/node/12.14.1/x64/bin/node]\r\n 2: 0x9dbd26 node::OnFatalError(char const*, char const*) [/opt/hostedtoolcache/node/12.14.1/x64/bin/node]\r\n 3: 0xb3af5a v8::Utils::ReportApiFailure(char const*, char const*) [/opt/hostedtoolcache/node/12.14.1/x64/bin/node]\r\n 4: 0xb3c4de v8::HandleScope::HandleScope(v8::Isolate*) [/opt/hostedtoolcache/node/12.14.1/x64/bin/node]\r\n 5: 0x94a98e node::InternalCallbackScope::InternalCallbackScope(node::Environment*, v8::Local<v8::Object>, node::async_context const&, node::InternalCallbackScope::ResourceExpectation) [/opt/hostedtoolcache/node/12.14.1/x64/bin/node]\r\n 6: 0x94b8a5 node::MakeCallback(v8::Isolate*, v8::Local<v8::Object>, v8::Local<v8::Function>, int, v8::Local<v8::Value>*, node::async_context) [/opt/hostedtoolcache/node/12.14.1/x64/bin/node]\r\n 7: 0x7f5245046527  [/home/runner/work/lodestar/lodestar/node_modules/gc-stats/build/gcstats/v1.4.0/Release/node-v72-linux-x64/gcstats.node]\r\n 8: 0x12d7951  [/opt/hostedtoolcache/node/12.14.1/x64/bin/node]\r\n 9: 0x12e9f58  [/opt/hostedtoolcache/node/12.14.1/x64/bin/node]\r\n10: 0x12d82db uv_run [/opt/hostedtoolcache/node/12.14.1/x64/bin/node]\r\n11: 0xa1ce80 node::NodeMainInstance::Run() [/opt/hostedtoolcache/node/12.14.1/x64/bin/node]\r\n12: 0x9acb68 node::Start(int, char**) [/opt/hostedtoolcache/node/12.14.1/x64/bin/node]\r\n13: 0x7f524d89bbf7 __libc_start_main [/lib/x86_64-linux-gnu/libc.so.6]\r\n14: 0x94a115  [/opt/hostedtoolcache/node/12.14.1/x64/bin/node]\r\